  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>Standard: Homogene dose plan</arm_group_label>
    <arm_group_type>Active Comparator</arm_group_type>
    <description>Treatment will be given over 33 treatments. The dose is 66 Gy.</description>
  </arm_group>
  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>Escalation: Inhomogene dose plan</arm_group_label>
    <arm_group_type>Experimental</arm_group_type>
    <description>Radiation dose is increased to tumor and lymph nodes based on an inhomogeneous dose distribution determined by the most active ( FDG-PET criteria ) area of the node compared to a standard uniform dose distribution.
Treatment will be given over 33 treatments. The dose is as high as possible taking the tolerance of the normal tissue into consideration</description>
  </arm_group>
